::Cygnar::
    He would've tilted his head to one side and laughed if he could.  Instead 
with his mouth still open, he laughed.  This was unexpected.  Unfortunately 
he hadn't planned on needing to prevent this event.  It still amused him 
because now no one could move.  Neither the attackers nor the defenders could 
move without the trap being disengaged.  So he stood and laughed.  Ignatius 
had just signed his own death certificate.  The others would want to kill him 
once they were released.
